 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Senior Motor Design Specialist ANDURIL INDUSTRIES Irvine, CA Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Anduril is a defense technology company, bringing Silicon Valley talent and funding to the defense sector. Our technology helps our customers solve their toughest challenges by enabling them to make better, more informed decisions in life-and-death situations. Weâ€™ve assembled a diverse team of experts in artificial intelligence, computer vision, sensor fusion, optics, and data analysis that are creating software and hardware solutions to radically evolve the capabilities of the United States and our allies. If you are passionate about solving problems that have real impact, come join Anduril and build the future of defense. 
 WHAT YOU'LL DO 
Responsible for electromagnetic analysis, modeling and design of electric motors for current and future products 
Own DFMEA and test procedures for electric motors components and completed assemblies 
Analysis and optimization with equations and finite element analysis on thermal and mechanical modeling 
Develop test plans and work with motor control and motor test engineers to validate motor performance predictions 
Define accelerated life tests, test conditions, and pass/fail criteria for all electric motors as well as completed system 
Creates DFMEA , technical reports, presentations, and participate in writing product documentation 
Collaboration with supply chain, vendor and manufacturing engineers 
 REQUIRED QUALIFICATIONS 
MS or Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering, Mechanical Engineering or the equivalent in experience with evidence of exceptional ability 
3+ years in electrical machine design & analysis with power rating up to 30 kW
 Extensive knowledge & experience required in electro-magnetic machine design using FEA tools, mesh networks, and analytical models 
Experience in electric vehicle powertrains, including various traction motor architectures 
Ability to troubleshoot and problem solve 
Knowledge of Altium Designer schematic and layout is a plus 
U.S. Person status is required as this position needs to access export controlled data 
